	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[Sanitising a work surface is a four-step process. As the name suggests, it combines cleaning and disinfection in single step.<br /><br />The first step is to pre-clean which includes removing food debris and waste.<br /><br />The next step is main clean using a clean cloth, hot water and a sanitiser in a clean bucket.<br /><br />A sanitiser is a cleaning chemical which combines both a detergent and a disinfectant.<br /><br />Remember not to place the bucket on the work surface. Alternatively, you may use a hand-spray. Allow sufficient contact time for effective disinfection.<br /><br />The third step will be rinsing, if required by the sanitiser manufacturer.<br /><br />The last step is drying; either air-dry or use a disposable paper towel.]]></transcript>	

